{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/why-we-need-cryptography-80c7f60b6c0c", "time": 1683008682.0665941, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/why-we-need-cryptography-80c7f60b6c0c/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Cryptography in data products. Beyond the trade-off between\u2026 | by Jan Osolnik | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Cryptography in data products", "description": "As data product technology matures, its potential to transform the substrate of our social structure does as well. Through our improved decision-making, it can move us towards higher well-being\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maslow%27s_hierarchy_of_needs", "anchor_text": "self-actualization", "paragraph_index": 1}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Social_Credit_System", "anchor_text": "surveillance state system", "paragraph_index": 2}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Digital_twin", "anchor_text": "describe the actual state of the networked system", "paragraph_index": 4}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Digital_signature", "anchor_text": "Digital signatures", "paragraph_index": 9}, {"url": "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/m/merkle-root-cryptocurrency.asp", "anchor_text": "Merkle roots", "paragraph_index": 9}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zero-knowledge_proof", "anchor_text": "zero-knowledge proof systems", "paragraph_index": 9}], "all_paragraphs": ["As data product technology matures, its potential to transform the substrate of our social structure does as well.", "Through our improved decision-making, it can move us towards higher well-being. Automation can provide more material abundance, less time involved in repetitive tasks, and thus more time for creative expression. To aim towards self-actualization is a modern luxury that most of our ancestors could never even dream of. The essence of our progress has been technological development.", "Yet technology is only a tool. Just as fire can both bake a steak but also burn down a house, so can technology be used for various means. It can be used to control the people to whom it is supposed to provide value. Cheap sensors and facial recognition algorithms are building blocks for the potential creation of a surveillance state system.", "This kind of governance guided by technology is enabled through the behavioral footprints of data. Society can be seen as a network with relationships (edges) between different individuals (nodes). Each individual can transmit data points that can be used to govern the network that they are a part of.", "Transparency of network behavior can be quantified with how well can the gathered data describe the actual state of the networked system. More transparency brings more potential to govern the future system state towards the desired outcome.", "As we have seen, top-down governance enabled by the transparency of data without privacy can be harmful. Transparency can be used for either social development or suppression. Either way, it can be a gamble not worth taking at the expense of our social liberties.", "While it\u2019s becoming more widely accepted that data products can transform the way we interact with each other, it\u2019s not as obvious with cryptography.", "Cryptography can be the missing link between collective efficiency and individual freedom, thus enabling the benefits of transparency while retaining our privacy", "Cryptographic primitives form building blocks that can be used in software systems for that aim.", "Digital signatures give us a trustable way to prove identity online by making the signature a function of the data that is signed. Merkle roots can capture the identity of information without revealing anything about the underlying information. And finally, zero-knowledge proof systems give us a tool for one party (the prover) to prove to another party (the verifier) that they know some information without sharing any of the information itself apart from the proof.", "Today, these form a core pillar for trustability in the design of crypto-economic systems. These early-adopters drive the maturation of the underlying technology. Soon, we might see growing adoption from public institutions with the newly available tools to build privacy-preserving data products. Anonymized, transparent, and open data that can be aggregated and used for governance. This can definitely make the trade-off between transparency and privacy more manageable to tackle.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes."], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2F80c7f60b6c0c&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fwhy-we-need-cryptography-80c7f60b6c0c&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fwhy-we-need-cryptography-80c7f60b6c0c&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fnew-story&source=---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------new_post_sidenav-----------", "anchor_text": "Write"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/search?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fwhy-we-need-cryptography-80c7f60b6c0c&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------